==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orion
<hw>O*ri"on</hw> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*r⟦imac⟧"⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'Wri`wn</grk>, orig., a celebrated hunter in the
oldest Greek mythology, after whom this constellation was named.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A large and bright constellation on the
equator, between the stars Aldebaran and Sirius. It contains a
remarkable nebula visible to the naked eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flaming glories of <qex>Orion's</qex> belt.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oriskany</ent>⟦br⟧
